- 'Chief patrons' refers to customers with the highest total spend;
- 'Generosity has been most felt' refers to the total amount of money spent by the customers;
- 'Treasures they have most generously funded' refers to the products that have generated the most revenue;
- 'Embarked on their journey to the buyers' refers to orders with a status of 'shipped'.

- "Outshone the average spenders" means customers who have spent more than the average total spend of all customers;
- "Top three treasures" refers to the top 3 products by total quantity sold;
- "Where these treasures will be delivered" means the default shipping address of the customer.

- "High-rollers" refers to customers who have placed more than 5 orders and whose total order value exceeds $1000;
- "Trips to the marketplace" refers to the number of orders placed by a customer;
- "Lavish spending" refers to the total order value;
- "Wallets" refers to the total order value of each customer.

- "top customers" refers to those with the highest spending percentage;
- "spending percentage" is calculated as the ratio of a customer's total spending to the total spending of all customers, multiplied by 100;
- "rank" is determined by the customer's position in the spending percentage distribution, with 0 being the lowest and 1 being the highest.
